U.S. Manufacturer Outlook Survey Fell This Quarter

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-09-15T21:34:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/u-s-manufacturer-outlook-survey-fell-this-quarter-table-.html
Overall manufacturing activity has
weakened in the U.S., according to the National Association of 
Manufacturers Business Outlook Survey. The results reflect the 
percentage of respondents who characterize the current business  
outlook as somewhat or very positive.  Primary Business Challenges and % of firms reporting:  Weaker domestic economy, sales 64.9%
Unfavorable business climate (taxes, regulations) 60.8%
Rising energy and raw material costs 51.4%  SOURCE:  National Association of Manufacturers   To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Tanzi in Washington at   atanzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  